      "review_summary": "The PR changes the cron failure-alert SQLite decoder to return an empty alert config when all optional alert columns are null.\n\nPR surface: Source +2. Total +2 across 1 file.\n\nReproducibility: yes. at source level: `bindFailureAlertColumns(undefined)` and `bindFailureAlertColumns({})` both produce null option columns, and the PR's unconditional `return {}` would make the no-config row decode as enabled. I did not run tests because this review is read-only.",
